<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-4984] camel-http does not send header values that are empty strings</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-4984</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;HttpProducer does not send HTTP header if header value from camel was an empty string.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is because ObjectHelper.createIterator(headerValue, null) will produce an empty iteration if headerValue is an empty string!&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12541384">CAMEL-4984</key>
            <summary>camel-http does not send header values that are empty strings</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
